SummaryEnglish: Game Grumps is a Shorty Award Let's Play webseries created on July 10, 2012, by comedic game critic Jon Jafari and animator Arin Hanson. Jafari left the show in June of 2013 to focus on his primary Youtube channel, JonTronShow. He was replaced by comedy musician Leigh Daniel Avidan, also known as "Danny Sexbang", from the musical comedy duo Ninja Sex Party. The channel also expanded to include new hosts: animator Ross O'Donovan, series editor Barry Nathan Kramer, and Suzy Berhow, Hanson's wife, in spin-offs along with editor Kevin Abernathy. Jafari and Hanson have said they were inspired to make the show after seeing episodes of James Rolfe's video game webseries The Angry Video Game Nerd. Game Grumps is a part of Polaris, a network owned by Maker Studios.

273.SummaryEnglish: In this episode, Arin again asks Dan if they can watch Cats (2019) together, and Dan says "yeah absolutely" really quickly and then moves onto the next topic, similar to the way you would answer your mom when she asks if you did your homework, when you really didn't. It seems Dan is not really that invested in seeing Cats with Arin, and I've been doing some serious soul searching trying to figure out why. It's causing me great agony and torment, and frankly causing my IBS to flare up, which is a whole thing in itself. One cannot be blamed for daydreaming about Arin and Dan leaving that theater together, grinning ear to ear as they skip down the sidewalk singing the Mr. Mistoffelees song in perfect harmony, and maybe stopping for frozen yogurt after. When you consider the fact that Dan is a huge furry and loves to boink people in animal costumes every day of his life, it really doesn't make much sense, and you have to wonder if Dan even really is a furry, or if his name is even really Dan Avidan? It could be Fred Von Pretzels or even Barack O'Neil. There is no way to know and tbh I'm freaking out. I don't even know what to do at this point.

49.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Our EMOTIONALLY STABLE RETURN
49.SummaryEnglish: Dan, now free from the shackles of heartache-induced turmoil, and with only a minor international pandemic weighing on his mind, resumes the role of LOAFUS CRAMWELL and takes us on FRESH DIVE into The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds.

50.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Fighting ADORABLE Little Enemies
50.SummaryEnglish: Loafus receives a bracelet that allows him to turn into a painting and sneak through tight spaces on the wall, which frankly makes zero sense from a physiological standpoint. I bet some of you freaks out there wish you could do the same though, amirite??????

51.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Arin's SICK Backstreet Boys Impression
51.SummaryEnglish: An aggressive elf wanders around shooting people with arrows and searching around in bushes for money.

52.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Daddy gets a BOSS FIGHT
52.SummaryEnglish: In which Arin tries to be a backseat gamer to Dan, who gets annoyed despite admitting that he's right.

53.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: We are THIRSTY for Link's Groin
53.SummaryEnglish: In which a discussion about Ikea meatballs leads to the dissolution of Dan and Arin's friendship.

54.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: This Game's Design is GENIUS
54.SummaryEnglish: If you don't watch this episode of Game Grumps... YOU TRIPPIN'!

55.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Is This The CUTEST Zelda Game
55.SummaryEnglish: In which Loafus ADORABLY utilizes the most PRECIOUS medieval weaponry to attack and brutalize the most LOVEABLE, HUGGABLE little murderous, evil demons.

56.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: We SAVE the TURTLE BABIES
56.SummaryEnglish: If Iron Maiden wrote songs with slightly cuter imagery, they probably would have written one about this episode.

57.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Please don't leave mean comments about this episode!
57.SummaryEnglish: Whoever designed this dungeon is one twisted sadistic NICE PERSON!

58.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: We're doing great, and feeling great!
58.SummaryEnglish: Brought to you by Butterfeet! The official candy bar of Game Grumps - The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds Episode 10.

59.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Zelda rap RETURNS!
59.SummaryEnglish: In which Dan makes many progresses but ultimately breaks his own brain!

60.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Arin picks the HOTTEST Backstreet Boy
60.SummaryEnglish: This dungeon has everything: venus fly traps on meth, medieval murder hornets, exploding cinderblocks. An embarassment of riches for Loafus and friends!

61.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Braving the dreaded WATER TEMPLE!
61.SummaryEnglish: If you don't mind the floaty electric skull squids and huge amphibious bugs that want to kill you, this place is downright pleasant!

62.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Arin being a SILLY GOOSE again
62.SummaryEnglish: Loafus stops by a fun museum and takes a nice long gander at the Mona Zelda!

63.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: This Dark Palace is REALLY DARK!
63.SummaryEnglish: Loafus slashing a big old cutie with his sword until it explodes? YES PLZ!

64.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: GAME GRUMPS IN 4D!
64.SummaryEnglish: So uh, we finished A Link Between Worlds at some point... and then life happened.

65.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Reliving our crappy playing!
65.SummaryEnglish: We watch in helpless frustration as we get slapped around by the giant slappy hand dude, and now we finally get what it's like to be a LOVELY!

66.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: It's a COLD SUMMER in the ICE DUNGEON
66.SummaryEnglish: PLUS: A special update about the future of Sonic Heroes on our channel!

67.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Arin ROASTS Dan while he steps away!
67.SummaryEnglish: Mother Maiamai: she makes weapons better, and she makes EPISODES BETTER!

68.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: Hilda lists her castle on Airbnb!
68.SummaryEnglish: World class accommodations, if you don't mind the myriad of little critters waiting around every corner to murder you!

69.TitleEnglish: The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds: VICTORY AT LAST for Loafus Cramwell
69.SummaryEnglish: The short, strange interdimensional Grumps escapade of watching themselves finally finish Zelda: A Link Between Worlds six weeks ago comes to a thrilling, heartwarming conclusion!

33.TitleEnglish: House Party: DEREK the Stair Keeper
33.SummaryEnglish: Some time ago a group of people were sitting in a restaurant, and one of them asked the others to say what they meant by Reality. There was much vague discussion, much talk of metaphysics and psychology, but one of those present, when asked his opinion, simply shrugged his shoulders and pointed at the saltshaker. He was amazed to find that no one understood him, yet he had intended to be neither clever nor obscure. His idea was just to give a commonsense answer to the question, on the ordinary assumption that Reality is whatever exists. He was not understood because his friends, in common with many others, regarded Reality as a special kind of existence and Life (with a capital L) as a particular way of living. Thus we often meet those who talk about the difference between being a mere clod, a mere animated stomach, and a real person; between those who simply exist and those who really live.

16.SummaryEnglish: The weird ass judge allows Mr. White to give three separate testimonies for some reason.

17.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Supernatural Baps
17.SummaryEnglish: Facing a lifetime of incarceration, Phoenix suffers a mental breakdown and begins to see spirits

18.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: A Spirited Defense
18.SummaryEnglish: Excited by good news, Maya completely flips out and forces herself into Phoenix's life permanently, and, spineless dingbat that he is, Wright just kind of goes with it.

19.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Turnabout Samurai
19.SummaryEnglish: In the Game Grumps' highly anticipated return to the Phoenix Wright series, Wright and Maya seemingly force their legal services on an actor who looks like he wants your pickle.

20.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: What I Got
20.SummaryEnglish: In this episode, which makes perfect narrative sense and in no way feels like the type of fever dream you have after you've spent all night on the toilet sick from eating an expired mutton chop in the blistering desert heat, the teenage Maya gives solid legal advice to Phoenix Wright, professional lawyer.

21.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Separate Stomachs
21.SummaryEnglish: In this episode of Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney, a game that was created by humans and was under no circumstances written and designed by aliens studying our species, Maya and Wright snoop around a famous actor's dressing room looking for snacks.

22.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Small Medium at Large
22.SummaryEnglish: Wright and Maya talk to the mysterious PA, and they suspect that she wants to go ga-doinga-doing-doing on Will Powers's shpedoinkle.

23.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Gas Grumps
23.SummaryEnglish: Our gassy legends burp, belch, and bellow their way through this humdinger of an episode, in which Dan makes reference to Mia's baps, and in perhaps the most stunning twist of the series yet, they change the text box transparency mid-game.

24.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Oldbag and Boujee
24.SummaryEnglish: Oldbag delivers one of the most insanely idiotic testimonies anyone has ever heard. At no point in her rambling, incoherent response, was she even close to anything that could be considered a rational thought. Everyone in the courtroom is now dumber for having listened to it. The judge awards her no points, and may God have mercy on her soul

25.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: The Power of the Oldbag
25.SummaryEnglish: Arin and Dan, in a moment of reckoning, admit to accusing a possibly innocent old woman of murder. In addition, Dan may or may not accuse Maya of wanting to take a dump on Phoenix for sexual gratification. This one's a roller coaster, folks.

26.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Troubled Girl
26.SummaryEnglish: Maya says a whole bunch of stuff that would indicate she's deeply unintelligent or at the very least ignorant, but in a stunning twist, she actually makes a good point.

27.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: You Gross, Sweaty Weirdo
27.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix and Maya encounter a gross, sweaty weirdo who somehow is able to communicate verbally in leetspeak, a delinquent child who really seems like he could benefit from some therapy, and a producer who seems to have been transported into this game from Winterfell.

28.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: HuFf PuFf
28.SummaryEnglish: This is a Guest Grumps with Larry the Cable Guy. Unfortunately, Larry takes off his flannel and gets butt nekkid in the Grump Room shortly into the episode, and Arin and Dan are forced to kick him out.

29.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: For Great Justice
29.SummaryEnglish: Arin and Dan beat the crap out of a young boy, and take great pleasure in doing so.

30.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: The Trial of Will Powers
30.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix fatshames Sal Monella during the course of his interrogation and honestly, it's unacceptable. Phoenix Wright... you're cancelled.

31.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: The Fallen Mrs. Monkey Head
31.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix Wright presses a little kid in all the right places.

32.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Homework
32.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix Wright grills a small child until he cries and gives up one of his possessions

33.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Excitable and Filled with Eggs
33.SummaryEnglish: Trapped in the Spoiler Owl's dungeon and forced to upload the episodes out of order, Ben did the only thing left to do in order to be set free... That's right, everyone - Ben had to blow the Spoiler Owl so we could finally see the missing Phoenix Wright episodes. Thank you for your sacrifice, Ben.

34.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Ah, The French
34.SummaryEnglish: Maya makes a startling realization about Dee Vasquez, moments after Arin and Danny discuss how hot she is.

35.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: The Spanish Inquisition
35.SummaryEnglish: In which Danny Sexbang, commonly referred to as Daniel Avidaniel, has a stroke mid-episode.

36.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: The Battle of Ellipsis
36.SummaryEnglish: Mia, clearly losing her grip on reality, encourages Phoenix to perform wrestling moves on Ms. Vasquez in the courtroom.

37.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Phoenix & Edgeworth: DATING?!
37.SummaryEnglish: Right at the climax of the big case, Phoenix seemingly has a stroke, changes his voice completely, chokes on his own spittle, and forgets how to speak. Danny, apparently forgetting that he is the World's Purest Soul, offers no sympathy, instead snapping at Phoenix to focus. Frankly, you hate to see it.

38.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Turnabout Goodbyes
38.SummaryEnglish: Edgeworth gets himself implicated in a serious crime, but in Phoenix's eyes, his only crime is not stripping off that tantalizing ascot and form fitting burgundy suit and going ham on his sweet patooter. Phoenix becomes so s*xually frustrated that he starts thirsting for Gumshoe. NOTE: Through forensic investigation, we found the missing episodes, but too close to posting time today for the video to be edited. We will be posting the three missing episodes over the next few days. We have also tracked down the cause and will be putting it on trial. It wasn't Ben. - Boruff

39.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Taking Poppers
39.SummaryEnglish: This episode will convince you more than ever that this game was indeed created and designed by real humans and definitely not by space aliens that are studying the human race from light years away.

40.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Your Hot, Dead Older Sister
40.SummaryEnglish: Gumshoe reveals that he, too, is smashing Edgeworth's sweet cakes to smithereens, and a passionate, fiery love triangle ensues

41.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Pretty Badgerlike
41.SummaryEnglish: In the midst of a tense conversation, Lotta admits to Phoenix that she would rather eat a skunk's booty like groceries than help him out with the case.

42.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Just Like Father
42.SummaryEnglish: Miles Edgeworth reveals to Phoenix that he's wearing a schnock ring and frankly....... ....... ....... I would like to see it

43.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Life Or Death For Poor Edgeworth
43.SummaryEnglish: You guys don't get a description for this episode, I'm on my lunch break. Sorry not sorry. Just watch the video it's really good.

44.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Pimp Hand Strong
44.SummaryEnglish: Some douchebag in Thomas Jefferson cosplay thinks he's better than everyone else and bosses people around in the courtroom.

45.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: More Like Bye-a
45.SummaryEnglish: Grumps: We remember absolutely nothing about this game. Also Grumps: Okay, here are the minute details of every single thing happening in this game.

46.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: By The Lake
46.SummaryEnglish: If Phoenix Wright could pretend that airplanes in the night sky were shooting stars, he would wish that everyone around him wasn't such a god damn moron.

47.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Showing The Enlargement
47.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix Wright racks his dense little brain to figure out the raging clue.

48.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Going Going Back Back To Gourd Lake Gourd
48.SummaryEnglish: Welcome back to the Danny and the Raptor show on KTLA 5!

49.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: All About The Bajjina
49.SummaryEnglish: In which Arin laughs uncontrollably at poor, sweet Danny exhibiting symptoms of disease. 1 like = 1 prayer for Danny's sneezy ass nose.

50.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: The Dirt On Gourdy
50.SummaryEnglish: A wang pump inadvertently becomes a crucial piece of evidence in this gripping, yet sexy episode of Phoenix Wright.

51.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: The Wet Noodle
51.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix and Maya descend upon a boat rental shop to engage in witness tampering, and encounter an old man who looks like he's about to drop the sickest skate tape of 2019, and promise him that they'll run his noodle store after he dies (?). Let's goooooooo0o!

52.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: I'm In Love With Edgeworth's Dad
52.SummaryEnglish: Edgeworth's father is revealed, and while it might be nice to suck his toes after you come home from school, that's unfortunately not possible, because he's dead. Deal with it.

53.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Tsk, Tsk, Tsk...
53.SummaryEnglish: A verdict is called, but conveniently a new witness appears out of thin air to throw everything into disarray. WHAT was the verdict? WHO is the mystery witness? WHY did the judge allow him to testify? WHEN are Phoenix and Edgeworth going to admit their love for each other? FIND OUT INSIDE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

54.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Alone On Christmas Eve
54.SummaryEnglish: The trial of the century continues as Larry Butz gives his gripping testimony about listening to the radio very loud.

55.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Are You Quite Mad?
55.SummaryEnglish: In a hail mary attempt to save the day, Phoenix reaches deep into his @$$ and comes up with a story so remarkably dumb that it just might be the truth.

56.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: A Memory... Of A Murder
56.SummaryEnglish: In an emotional monologue, Larry Butz reveals to Phoenix and Maya that he got cancelled in third grade.

57.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Examine The Squawkin' Parrot
57.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix and Maya get a raging clue.

58.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Edgeworth Tells All
58.SummaryEnglish: I can't even deal with the crazy s#$% that Edgeworth talks about in this episode. Like, it's crazy, bro. Just.... wow.

59.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Polly Want A Lawyer
59.SummaryEnglish: You asked for it and you got it - a Phoenix Wright episode that lasts longer than many marriages in this day and age. Enjoy!

60.TitleEnglish: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney: Von Karma's A Beeyotch
60.SummaryEnglish: Phoenix, Von Karma, Maya, Butz, Edgeworth, Gumshoe... the gang is all here for the thrilling conclusion to this long, strange journey, and we'd like to thank you all for coming along for the ride by mailing each of you a stick of gum. Enjoy!
